+Strong instruction following and strict JSON compliance are critical because the UI parses the response directly. Long-context reliability matters because the system prompt, CROSS results, row context, conversation history, and tariff methodology can be several thousand tokens. Legal/tax-like reasoning matters because HTS classification is structured, precedent-sensitive, and rule-driven. The model should be good at comparing alternatives, declining uncertainty, and identifying when a CROSS ruling is similar in appearance but different in essential character. Stable low-temperature behavior is preferable to creative language generation.
